   * a set of n labelled objects into k nonempty unlabelled subsets.
   * stirlingS2 only takes integer arguments.
   * The following condition must be enforced: k <= n.
   *
   *  If n = k or k = 1 <= n, then s(n,k) = 1
   *  If k = 0 < n, then s(n,k) = 0
   *
